      <p>\"Operated 6 prime movers on peak hours only. Constant congestion, wasted fuel, driver stress. Heard about RM15 off-peak incentive. Ing Heng financed 2 additional prime movers (0% down) dedicated to off-peak. Installed OBU on all 8 prime movers. Trained drivers for night shifts. Now 4 prime movers run off-peak, 4 remain peak. Off-peak incentive: RM3,000/month. Fuel savings (no congestion): RM1,500/month. Bonus: can fit 3rd off-peak trip when demand high. Monthly profit up RM6,000. 0% down preserved RM84,000 used for OBU installation, driver night shift training. Off-peak transformation was best business decision.\"</p>
      <p><em>— Zainal Abidin, Operations Director</em></p>

      <h3>Cross-Border Off-Peak Specialist</h3>

      <p>\"Singapore-Thailand route. Border crossings unpredictable—sometimes 1 hour, sometimes 6 hours. Peak hour border waits wasted 3+ hours. Shifted operations to off-peak: 10pm-2am border crossings. Reduced wait times to 1 hour average. Saved 2 hours per trip = 2 additional trips possible daily. Off-peak incentive: RM2,250/day (5 prime movers × 3 trips × RM15). Revenue increase: RM15,000/day (additional trips). Financed 5 prime movers with Ing Heng (0% down), included OBUs. Higher monthly installment but profit increase RM40,000/month. Off-peak strategy transformed margin.\"</p>
      <p><em>— Steven Boon, Managing Director</em></p>

