      <h3>Step 1: Calculate Current Trip Profitability</h3>

      <p>For each prime mover:
      <br>• Trips per day
      <br>• Revenue per trip
      <br>• Fuel cost per trip
      <br>• Driver cost per trip
      <br>• Current net profit per trip</p>

      <h3>Step 2: Project Off-Peak Profitability</h3>

      <p>With off-peak incentive:
      <br>• Same revenue per trip
      <br>• Reduced fuel cost (no congestion)
      <br>• RM15 incentive per trip
      <br><strong>Compare:</strong> Off-peak profit vs peak profit</p>

      <h3>Step 3: Assess Operational Feasibility</h3>

      <p>Evaluate:
      <br>• Client acceptance of off-peak deliveries
      <br>• Port/warehouse off-peak access
      <br>• Driver willingness for night shifts
      <br>• Dispatcher availability</p>

      <h3>Step 4: Finance Off-Peak Setup</h3>

      <p>Work with financier to:
      <br>• Finance prime movers dedicated to off-peak
      <br>• Include OBU equipment in financing
      <br>• Structure payments based on off-peak revenue (incentive included)</p>

      <h2>The Bottom Line: Off-Peak = Bonus Profit</h2>

      <p>The RM15/trip off-peak incentive isn't just a bonus—it's a profitability multiplier:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Direct Incentive:</strong> RM15/trip pure profit
        <li><strong>Fuel Savings:</strong> RM500-RM1,000 monthly (no congestion)
        <li><strong>Time Savings:</strong> Opportunity for additional trips
        <li><strong>Driver Retention:</strong> Less stress = lower turnover</li>
      </ul>

      <p>0% down payment financing accelerates off-peak transition. OBU equipment included in financing. Incentive earnings exceed transition costs within 60 days.</p>

